      "source": [
        "## QUESTION\n",
        "\n",
        "1. __Take time to get to know your data.__ Based on some initial exploration, identify 3 variables in the dataset you think will have strong predictive ability for determining if a house was built before 1980. Explain/justify the reasoning behind your guesses (for example with plots).\n",
        "\n",
        "The three variables I think would be helpful is the living area, finished basement, and condition of the house. These don't have a huge correlation, but I think all together they could be helpful."
      ],
      "id": "d11c35b5"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Optional: code you used to get to know your data\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Dataset shape:', dwellings.shape)\n",
        "for c in dwellings.columns:\n",
        "    print(c)\n",
        "print(dwellings.select(pl.col(\"yrbuilt\", \"stories\", \"before1980\")))\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_data = dwellings.select(['yrbuilt', 'livearea', 'finbsmnt', 'condition_AVG']).to_pandas()\n",
        "\n",
        "p1 = (\n",
        "    ggplot(plot_data, aes(x='yrbuilt', y='livearea'))\n",
        "    + geom_point(alpha=0.2, size=2)\n",
        "    + labs( title = 'Year Built vs Living Area', x = 'Year Built', y = 'Living Area')\n",
        "    + scale_x_continuous(format='{d}')\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "p2 = (\n",
        "    ggplot(plot_data, aes(x='yrbuilt', y='finbsmnt'))\n",
        "    + geom_point(alpha=0.2, size=2)\n",
        "    + labs( title = 'Year Built vs Finished Basement', x = 'Year Built', y = 'Finished Basement')\n",
        "    + scale_x_continuous(format='{d}')\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "p3 = (\n",
        "    ggplot(plot_data, aes(x='yrbuilt'))\n",
        "    + geom_bar()\n",
        "    + labs( title = 'Count of Houses by Year Built', x = 'Year Built', y = 'Count')\n",
        "    + scale_x_continuous(format='{d}')\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "plot_grid = gggrid([p1, p2, p3], ncol=1)\n",
        "plot_grid"
      ],
      "id": "156d364f",
