    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "1. __Build a classification model labeling houses as being built “before 1980” or “during or after 1980”.__ Your goal is to reach or exceed 90% accuracy. Report your final model choice and any other model parameters you may have tweaked (train-test split ratio, tuning parameters, etc).  \n",
        "\n",
        "Here we're able to use RandomForestClassifier to predict whether a house was built before 1980. I used few features at first and then increased the number of features to see if it would increase the accuracy -- it did, by about 3%. I tweaked the train-test ratio to 70-30 and that seemed to work well, but I didn't do any tuning of the model parameters. I think that could be a next step to try to increase the accuracy even more."
      ],
      "id": "db274422"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Include and execute your code here\n",
        "# Don't forget, you need another import statement to import the desired ML model from sklearn\n",
        "features = dwellings.select(['livearea','finbsmnt','basement','stories','nocars','numbdrm','numbaths','condition_AVG',\n",
        "    'quality_A','quality_B','quality_C','quality_D','quality_X',\n",
        "    'gartype_Att','gartype_Det','gartype_None','gartype_CP']).to_numpy()\n",
        "target = dwellings.select('before1980').to_numpy().ravel()\n",
        "\n",
        "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(features, target, test_size=0.3, stratify=target)\n",
        "\n",
        "model = RandomForestClassifier()\n",
        "model.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
        "\n",
        "y_pred = model.predict(x_test)\n",
        "\n",
        "acc = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "print('accuracy:', acc)"
      ],
